'''Alumina Partners of Jamaica''', also known as '''Alpart''', is a company that owns and operates a bauxite refinery in [[Nain, Jamaica]].<ref name="usgs">[http://minerals.usgs.gov/minerals/pubs/country/2006/myb3-2006-ac-aa-bf-bb-bd-do-dr-gj-jm-mh-nt-sc-vc-td.pdf 2006 Minerals Yearbook: Islands of the Caribbean]. [[United States Geological Survey]].</ref> Alpart was founded in 1969 as a joint venture by [[Kaiser Aluminum]], [[Reynolds Aluminum]], and [[Anaconda Copper|Anaconda]].<ref name="unsettled">[http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20080525/cleisure/cleisure2.html Unsettled time for bauxite/alumina] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080928063155/http://www.jamaica-gleaner.com/gleaner/20080525/cleisure/cleisure2.html |date=2008-09-28 }}. Carlton E. Davis. ''Jamaica Gleaner.''</ref> Alpart exports 1.65 million tonnes of alumina overseas per year, and earned gross revenues of [[United States dollar|US$]]1.3 billion in 2007.<ref name="crisis">[http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/news/html/20081109T190000-0500_142367_OBS_GLOBAL_ECONOMIC_CRISIS_HITS_ALPART.asp Global economic crisis hits Alpart] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081113132537/http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/news/html/20081109T190000-0500_142367_OBS_GLOBAL_ECONOMIC_CRISIS_HITS_ALPART.asp |date=2008-11-13 }}. Garfield Myers. ''Jamaica Observer.''</ref> As of 2011, previous partner Hydro divested its 35% stake to [[Rusal]] which assumed 100% stake in Alpart, wholly owned by [[RusAl]] the refinery has paused operations due to the company's alumina product experiencing a drastic 60 per cent price reversal since July 2008 with the temporary shutdown allowing the plant to be prepared for future developments that may see the industry emerging from the economic downturns it has faced.<ref name="unsettled" />
In 2016, UC Rusal sold 100% stake of the Alumina Partners of Jamaica (‘Alpart’) to the Chinese state industrial group, JIUQUAN IRON & STEEL (GROUP) Co. Ltd. (‘JISCO’).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.basel.ru/en/sectornews/rusal_19_07_2016/|title=RUSAL sells Alpart alumina refinery in Jamaica|website=www.basel.ru|language=ru|access-date=2017-06-09}}</ref>
